name: Caitlyn
title: the Sheriff of Piltover
shortBio: Renowned as its finest peacekeeper, Caitlyn Kiramman is also Piltover's best shot at ridding the city of its elusive criminal elements. She is often paired with Vi, acting as a cool counterpoint to her partner's more impetuous nature. Even though she carries a one-of-a-kind hextech rifle, Caitlyn's most powerful weapon is her superior intellect, allowing her to lay elaborate traps for any lawbreakers foolish enough to operate in the City of Progress.

skins.name: Resistance Caitlyn
skins.description: Caitlyn has never forgiven herself for letting Viktor's rise to power go unchecked for so long. Determined to fire the shot that ends the war for good, she has personally gunned down hundreds of Battlecast machines in her bloody search for absolution.

skins.name: Sheriff Caitlyn
skins.description: The Old West lies far outside the government's jurisdiction, leaving local peacekeepers to enforce whatever passes for justice on the high frontier. As lone sheriff of the town of Progress, Caitlyn has found that the arm of the law is roughly as long as the range of her rifle.

skins.name: Safari Caitlyn
skins.description: When she isn't attending galas or teaching seminars, Dr. Caitlyn Kiramman can be found exploring ancient ruins in search of historical artifacts. Armed with her trusty rifle, a wealth of esoteric knowledge, and an accident-prone Ezreal, she braves the most mysterious places in the world to bring long-dead civilizations and their secrets into the light.

skins.name: Arctic Warfare Caitlyn
skins.description: Very few snipers can cut it on the Arctic front. The cold is unforgiving, the winds are harsh, and any who dare brave the tundra find themselves at the mercy of Caitlyn, a sniper with deadly aim and a killer instinct.

skins.name: Officer Caitlyn
skins.description: Most people assume that Caitlyn is the "good cop" between her and Vi. What they don't know is that her sharp eyes, quick wit, and dedication make her one of the toughest officers on the force. She doesn't mind being underestimated, especially if it gives her the upper hand.

skins.name: Headhunter Caitlyn
skins.description: Caitlyn's arsenal of alien weaponry isn't meant to level the playing field. It's to ensure that every hunt, every target, and every shot she takes goes exactly the way she wants it to.

skins.name: Lunar Wraith Caitlyn

chromas.name: Lunar Wraith Caitlyn

descriptions.description: Loot exclusive gained from the 2018 Lunar Revel missions.

chromas.description: Loot exclusive gained from the 2018 Lunar Revel missions.

skins.description: A malignant spirit said to appear during Lunar Revel, Caitlyn is known to meddle in the affairs of gods and mortals alike. Her attention has been catastrophic to all who draw it, and even seeing her is considered an ill omen.

skins.name: Pulsefire Caitlyn

chromas.name: Pulsefire Caitlyn

descriptions.description: This chroma was released as a Loot exclusive in the 2020 Pulsefire event.

chromas.description: This chroma was released as a Loot exclusive in the 2020 Pulsefire event.

skins.description: A legendary chrono-law enforcer feared in every age, Caitlyn's mission is to protect the fragile enigma that is time. Those who dare threaten its integrity inevitably find themselves firmly locked in the sights of her temporal plasma blaster.

skins.name: Pool Party Caitlyn

chromas.name: Pool Party Caitlyn

descriptions.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive in 2021.

chromas.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive in 2021.

skins.description: For Caitlyn, nothing says a perfect summer's day like lounging at a luxurious poolside, eating shaved ice and drinking tropical libations. And shooting people. She really loves shooting people.

skins.name: Arcade Caitlyn
skins.description: Acclaimed hero of the “Sniper Cop” rail shooter series, Caitlyn enforced the laws of Arcadia prior to the Battle Boss uprising. She brings her sharp eye and eager trigger finger to the fight to save her world, only stopping long enough to flick her gun off-screen for a reload.

skins.name: Prestige Arcade Caitlyn
skins.description: Appearing most recently in “Sniper Cop 7” as a golden-clad secret character, Caitlyn's popularity has finally transcended games as a medium.

skins.name: Battle Academia Caitlyn

chromas.name: Battle Academia Caitlyn

descriptions.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive in 2021.

chromas.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive in 2021.

skins.description: A feared and respected second year, head of the Luminary Club, and class president of Labrys God-Weapon Academy. Caitlyn enrolled herself in the famously troubled school specifically to whip the delinquents there into prime fighting shape, hoping to one day become the greatest battlefield general in history. With her perfect record, she's not too far off.

skins.name: Prestige Arcade Caitlyn (2022)
skins.description: Appearing most recently in “Sniper Cop 7” as a golden-clad secret character, Caitlyn's popularity has finally transcended games as a medium.

skins.name: Snow Moon Caitlyn

chromas.name: Snow Moon Caitlyn

descriptions.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive in 2022.

chromas.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive in 2022.

skins.description: A tool of chilling acuity, Caitlyn is the Snow Moon's most elite sniper. It was her craving for a calculating nature, stripped of the moorings of sympathy, that drew her to serve. There was once warmth in her heart; in dreams, she sees a figure, wild and untamed, in a world not meant for her.

skins.name: Heartthrob Caitlyn

chromas.name: Heartthrob Caitlyn

descriptions.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive in 2023.

chromas.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive in 2023.

skins.description: I hate the way you walk around, like you're Princess Caitlyn of the mall, and I'm just some gutter rat. I hate the way you look at me when there's no one else around, but wouldn't be caught dead with me in town. Maybe our whole thing was just a huge mistake. So if you want me to go, I'm gone. But ask, and I will stay. -Vi

chromas.name: DRX Caitlyn

chromas.description: This chroma was released as a bundle exclusive during DRX World Championship showcase.

skins.description: Honoring Deft's winning performance as Caitlyn during the 2022 World Championship.

skins.name: Arcane Commander Caitlyn

chromas.name: Arcane Commander Caitlyn

descriptions.description: This chroma was released as an exclusive drop from The Sanctum.

chromas.description: This chroma was released as an exclusive drop from The Sanctum.

skins.description: Driven by a newfound desire for revenge, Caitlyn's principles have crumbled, leaving no room for hope or peace as tensions with Zaun continue to escalate. Her single-minded focus is on bringing Jinx to justice. But beneath the grief and guilt, doubt begins to creep in: is the cost of vengeance truly worth it?

skins.name: Prestige Arcane Commander Caitlyn

chromas.name: Prestige Arcane Commander Caitlyn

descriptions.description: This chroma was released as a Loot exclusive in the Arcane event.

chromas.description: This chroma was released as a Loot exclusive in the Arcane event.

skins.description: As scion of the Kiramman family, Caitlyn knows how to command respect from the moment she enters a room—not only with her sharp appearance, but her even-sharper gaze as well. Having climbed the ranks to lead the city's enforcers, she makes an even stronger asset to the future of Piltover.

passive.name: Headshot
passive.description: Every few basic attacks, or against a target she has trapped or netted, Caitlyn will fire a headshot dealing bonus damage that scales with her critical strike chance. On trapped or netted targets, Caitlyn's Headshot attack range is doubled.

spells.name: Piltover Peacemaker
spells.description: Caitlyn revs up her rifle for 1 second to unleash a penetrating shot that deals physical damage (deals less damage to subsequent targets).
spells.dynamicDescription:
Caitlyn revs her rifle to fire a piercing shot dealing @InitialDamage@ physical damage. After the bolt strikes the first target, it opens into a wider shot that deals @SecondaryDamage@ physical damage.

Enemies revealed by Yordle Snap Trap always take full damage.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: Yordle Snap Trap
spells.description: Caitlyn sets a trap that, when sprung, reveals and immobilizes the enemy champion for 1.5 seconds, granting Caitlyn an empowered Headshot.
spells.dynamicDescription: Caitlyn sets a trap that <status>Roots</status> the first champion that steps on it for @Effect6Amount@ seconds and granting <keywordStealth>True Sight</keywordStealth> of them for 3 seconds. Traps last for @Effect3Amount@ seconds, and @Effect5Amount@ traps may be active at once. This Ability has @Effect5Amount@ charges (@AmmoRechargeTime@ second refresh).@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: 90 Caliber Net
spells.description: Caitlyn fires a heavy net to slow her target. The recoil knocks Caitlyn back.
spells.dynamicDescription: Caitlyn fires a net, pushing her backwards. The net <status>Slows</status> the first target hit by @Effect3Amount@% for @Effect2Amount@ second and deals <magicDamage>@NetDamage@ magic damage</magicDamage>.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@

spells.name: Ace in the Hole
spells.description: Caitlyn takes time to line up the perfect shot, dealing massive damage to a single target at a huge range. Enemy champions can intercept the bullet for their ally.
spells.dynamicDescription:
Caitlyn takes a moment to channel and line up the perfect shot, then she fires, dealing @RTotalDamage@ physical damage, but other enemy champions can intercept it. This Ability grants True Sight of the target during the channel.

Deals up to an additional @CritChanceAmp*100@% based on Caitlyn's Critical Strike chance.@SpellModifierDescriptionAppend@
